{FLAVOR}It's important to avoid stereotyping as much as possible. Stereotypes are often flat-out wrong. And also hurtful. But honestly ... Banana Launcher is TOTALLY bananas.
Banana Launchers can fire explosive bananas at any tile on the lawn.
Tap on banana, then a tile, to launch explosive banana
{FLAVOR}Blastberry Vine snickers to himself. He imagines lobbing bomblets. He’s been reading up on it and he knows it’s gonna make a big splash when it happens. “Soon,” he whispers.
Blastberry Vines can be planted on top of other plants to provide increased defense and an additional attack in the form of lobbed projectiles that break into explosive bomblets.
{FLAVOR}"Hey, guys! Blockoli here! What's goin' on? Here comes a zombie! I'm gonna SLAM 'IM! With FISTS!" says Blockoli. And he really means it!
Blockoli dual-wields two sturdy floret shields, slamming them down to stun and block approaching zombies.
{FLAVOR}As the first new member to your home defense team, Bloomerang enjoys long walkabouts with his friend, Koala Bear, and listening to his Bob Barley albums out back.
Bloomerangs can hit multiple targets in their lane, twice each coming and going!
Throws many boomerangs that hit all the zombies to the left, right, above, and below.
Hits up to three targets in its lane, twice

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT} damage increases across multiple Blooming Hearts

{FLAVOR}Blooming Heart loves zombies. She gets guff from her fellow plants over it, but she stands firm. She's into zombies and makes no apologies about it.
Blooming Hearts lob projectiles that infatuate zombies, causing increasing damage the more they hit.
Lobs projectiles that do more damage the more they hit

{KEYWORD}Usage: {STAT}single use, instant
{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}blows away all flying zombies

{FLAVOR}The luckiest stunt clover around, Blover is the most recent recipient of the Stunty Award. You can see his work in "Bulb Fiction," "Rooty," and "Finding Flower." He also teaches a stunt class on Tuesdays at the community center.
Blovers blow away all zombies in the air.
Blows away all flying and floating zombies

{KEYWORD}Usage: {STAT}heavily damages octopuses, surfboards & gravestones
{KEYWORD}Usage: {STAT}destroys chickens & weasels
{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}affects whole board on planting, single lane afterward
{FLAVOR}Boingsetta's a springy plant whose positive outlook is infectiously delightful! The chilling effect is merely a secondary consequence.
Boingsettas slam the ground in a "boing" that heavily damages grid items, bounces zombies back and chills them.

{FLAVOR}Guess which team has won the League Championship for five years running now? Team Bowling Bulb, that's who. They are on a ROLL. You and your pals think you got what it takes to stop 'em? Yeah, sure. Keep dreamin, bub.

{FLAVOR}Bramble Bush is a prickly sort. In fact, let's not beat around the Bramble Bush here; he's covered in extraordinarily dangerous spikes.
Bramble Bush traps and damages a zombie.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}creates buttering butter splats

{FLAVOR}Buttercup's sweet as can be, but she packs a wallop! "I'm not cheap," she says, referring to her flat 25 sun cost. "I'm reasonable."
Buttercup butters butter onto attacking zombies, stunning them with butter. Butter!
{FLAVOR}Cabbage-pult received his doctorate in pulting from Harvest University. He knows a thing or two about launching his way to the top. He also makes a mean soup.
Cabbage-pults hurl cabbages at the enemy.
Hits every zombie on the lawn with a large cabbage.
Hurls cabbages over obstacles at the enemy

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}hides and does ground damage when zombies are near

{FLAVOR}You might remember Chard Guard from his days in the WWF (that's World Wrestling Foliage). When he was in the ring – boy-oh-boy – he was something to behold! His moves! His style! His attitude! The crowd loved him. He was quite the star for a while there. Sure, those days are behind him. But if you watch carefully, when Chard Guard is fighting zombies, you'll see him use the wrestling move he made famous. The ol' Knock 'Em Dead maneuver – it gets 'em every time.
Chard Guards are defensive blockers that can hurl zombies backwards.
Returns to full health, then damages and pushes back zombies in 6 adjacent tiles.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}moderate delay between chomps

{FLAVOR}Everyone appreciates what Chomper does. His appetite has saved them on numerous occasions. But truth be told, Chomper's friends think that eating zombies is gross. And his breath! No one has the heart to tell him, and he never gets the hint when you offer him a mint.
Chompers can devour a zombie whole, but they are vulnerable while chewing.

{FLAVOR}As the owner and primary user of "Vitamin C-U-Later" 20-hour energy shots, Citron is always on and always ready for action. "Let's make this happen!!"

Their team spirit is too overwhelming!
Gamers in a game? Too meta!
Barrels are for storing things, not for smushing plants!
Time to get back to basics, and thin out the zombie horde!
Their pompadours and bikinis may be stylish, but they're still brain-eaters!
Defeat Basic Big Wave Beach Zombies!
Teach these zombies that buckets are for making sand castles.
Better beat these beach blanket bozos!
They're zombies, but they look like weird crabs! Ick!
Half fish, half imp. Entirely gross.
Their headgear is simply too geometric!
Their emotions are too raw, too honest!
Their fly moves are simply intolerable!
Time to make these zombies kick the bucket!
Bug/zombie symbiosis is just too creepy!
They look like bulls, but they're actually robots! GET 'EM!
Bones in beards are questionably fashionable!
That camel-flauge isn't fooling anyone. Show those zombies they can't hide from you!
They wrangled just one too many chickens!
Practice a little garden safety by culling out Conehead Zombies!
These cow-punching, boot-wearing ghouls need some good ol' fashioned frontier justice!
In my day, buckets were for mucking the stables!
Send these cone rangers to the pokey!
Those weird skulls shouldn't be able to do what they do!
They're not pleasant, they're peasant! And that's terrible!
They'll never be knights with low-tier equipment like that!
Their big stone hammers are clumsy and all too effective!
These monks ain't funky! Except for their smell.
Zombie like cone. You not a zombie. Crush cone!
Their mean little giggles are super unsettling!
Their 70s disco rhythms don't belong in their far-future era!
Who knew dodos could be such jerks?
Bare-headed, cone-wearing or bucket-bearing, these basic bandaged brutes have got to go!
These pail-packers need to go pound sand!
Don't they have a pyramid to build, or something?
Wrap things up by taking care of some Mummified Gargantuars!
They're always growling about obscure bands!
Defeat Basic Neon Mixtape Tour Zombies!
They don't know what it means to be a metalhead!
Their traffic cone and denim look is SO out of style.
They need to learn at least two chords!
Shovels just shouldn't be that effective! Punish them!
Use your leveled-up plants to tackle extra-tough veteran zombies in expert levels! Warning: May Be Tense!
Somebody needs to teach these zombies that playing with fire is dangerous. That somebody is you!
Because seriously. These guys. They need to go away.
How dare they shove your plants like they do?
A skull on a head is one skull too many!
They have shiny jumpsuits and awful, carnivorous intentions!
They need to upgrade to the zCone 7 anyway.
They have telephone poles for arms! TELEPHONE POLES!
They scamper around in creepy little spider-bots! Brrrrrr!
Take on the big boys by taking out some random Gargantuars!
Roller skates are more of a 70s thing anyway!
Because snowballs are preposterous hunting gear!
They lack technological sophistication! Punish them for it!
I've heard of ice buckets, but this is ridiculous!
They're all just evolutionary dead ends!
These lunkheads don't even have the decency to be slothful!
Unfortunately these yetis are anything but scarce.
How do they pack all those zombies in there? It strains credulity!
These things are just weird. Please get rid of them!
Why do they get jetpacks? It's so unfair!
They're constantly ripping off other funnier zombies' material!
They refuse to govern with the consent of the governed!
They work too hard upholding a regressive feudal system!
Nobody should have ever issued them a license to fly!
Their exploratory efforts are highly questionable!
Buckets. Why did it have to be buckets?
Impressive mustache or no, these guys have got to go!
They just lug too much stuff around!
Their helmets are just the piths!
How dare they spin their mics that way!
Robo-cone zombies are too cylindrical to be allowed!
Their contemporary crimes may not be countenanced!
Make them kick the… well, you know.
A traffic cone is a timeless look for a zombie. But you're not a zombie, so smash 'em!
They're really just big softies. Make sure they know that.
They already threw out the comics section!
Enslaving octopuses for zombie purposes is just not cool!
Those parasols are just too fancy and expensive!
These Pharaohs think that they rule, but they'll never defeat you in a duel!
They can't even read sheet music!
Swab the decks with their leaky headgear!
Do it before they mutate into Pirate Admiral Zombies!
Cross their crossbones off the list!
Turn these cannoneers into cannon fodder!
What are they hiding under their ponchos? You can never tell!
And defeat their scruffy prospector beards, too!
E.M.Peaches make short work of these technological terrors!
Their jackets and boots have too many spikes!
Ra Zombies are out to soak up your sun - time to make them ancient history!
Teach them it's better to leave relics where they are!
How can a seagull that small carry a zombie? It's ridiculous!
They wear snorkels when they don't even need to breathe!
They're throwing away a perfectly good post-secondary education!
Who do they think they are, buckling those swashes?
It's time for these Tomb Raisers to learn that messing with you was a grave mistake!
What secrets are contained within its lunchbox? Only one way to find out!
That iceblock-shoving trick of theirs is way over the line.
Who hoards weasels inside a log? WHO???
Get them before they get you!
Their dark transformative powers must not be abided!

{FLAVOR}Barrel Roller Zombie is part of a super underground secret awesome club. You probably haven't heard of it. Also, his left arm is slightly longer than his right arm.
His rolling barrel crushes plants and provides excellent protection.
{FLAVOR}Go to the beach, they said. Put a cone on your head, they said. So, yeah, that's what Pompadour Conehead did. He's at his best when following simple instructions.
His starfish cone gives him twice the toughness of a normal pompadour zombie.

{FLAVOR}Pompadour Buckethead tried to learn to play the ukulele. He figured it would be easier to learn than the guitar on account of how small it is. But his stiff fingers ... they just weren't made for it. Now he just bangs on his bucket. And he's not half-bad either.
His scallop shelled bucket gives him great resistance to damage.

{FLAVOR}Pompadour Zombie recently noticed that he was wearing only one flip-flop. He THINKS he lost the other one while doing the limbo at a bonfire party the other night. But to be honest, that entire night is a little hazy ... and that flip-flop could be anywhere.

{FLAVOR}See that starfish on Bikini Conehead's cone? She put that there herself. She gets a lot of compliments on it too. And sure enough, now it seems like everyone is accessorizing with starfish. She's a trendsetter, that one.
Her starfish cone makes her twice as tough as a basic bikini zombie.

{FLAVOR}Bikini Buckethead had big ambitions. She wanted to do more than just lurch around on a beach all day. Her life's dream: to perform internationally with a synchronized swimming team. Sadly, the nose plug was her undoing. If she only had a nose ...
Her scallop shelled bucket provides great protection from damage.

{FLAVOR}Is it weird that we haven't seen any female zombies before? Some say yes. Some say no. Either way, Bikini Zombie is used to breaking new ground. She's not afraid to go where no woman zombie has gone before. You could call her a pioneer. You could call her a hero.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}pulls plants to the right
{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}plants next to him are tossed off the lawn

{FLAVOR}Everyone is tired of Fisherman Zombie's fishing stories. He's always bragging about the size of his catch. Time and time again, he claims to have caught "the big one." But the fact of the matter is, no one has seen him actually catch a fish. Not once. It's more than a little suspicious.
Casts his line to pull far plants to him.

{FLAVOR}Talk about a disgruntled zombie. Beach Flag Zombie is fed up. None of the other zombies seem to appreciate just how difficult it is for him to swim while holding a flag. Not once have they thanked him for doing the hard work that needs to be done. So it shouldn't come as a surprise: He's been interviewing for jobs elsewhere.
Marks the arrival of a huge wet "wave" of zombies.

{KEYWORD}Damage: {STAT}crushes plants with driftwood
{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}launches Imp Mermaid when damaged

{FLAVOR}This big guy loves the water. When he's deep down in it, he feels light as a feather. He feels like he's flying. Most importantly, during those precious moments, he feels as if the weight of Imp Mermaid Zombie has been lifted from his shoulders.
Titanic zombie who isn't shellfish with his might.

{FLAVOR}Imp Mermaid Zombie couldn't decide whether to wear the top made out of coconut shells or the top made out of seashells. She went with the slinky coconut-shell number because, really, the seashells are soooo last wave.
Washes in past your defenses, then flounders forward.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}bound plants are passive until their octopus is destroyed

{FLAVOR}It started innocently enough. One day, Octo Zombie decided to get a pet octopus. But he loved that octopus so much, he got another and another ... and another. Next thing you know, he was volunteering at an octopus rescue shelter. And now, well, no one wants to tell him, but he's pretty much the undersea equivalent of a cat lady. You should see how many are living at his house. It's quite startling.
Throws octopi at your plants to bind them up.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}submerges to avoid attacks

{FLAVOR}Snorkel Zombie has a hard time getting the Bikini Zombies. He's tried offering them flowers, jewelry, and even chocolate-covered brains. But nothing seems to work. They just can't seem to see past the snorkel on his face.

{KEYWORD}Damage: {STAT}can crush a plant with his board

{FLAVOR}Surfer Zombie took up surfing just last year. At first, he only did it because he thought it would make him look cool. But he was a natural. Now he can hang 10 with the best of them. Now he's headed to the pro circuit. Now he IS cool.
Surfs past plants on the water, then carries board on land.

It is a fact that everyone loves clowns, and zombies, and therefore clown zombies.
The pointy cone provides extra protection for this jolly fellow.
It turns out miniature elephants are a much greater challenge to train than the regular-sized ones. This is especially true if the trainer is a zombie and has no mind.

You're going to want to keep an eye out for that monkey.
Grinderbox helmet provides extra defense against attack, houses a monkey.

Carnie Zombie loves the freedom of the open road and would never ever cheat you.
A hard and honest worker at a hard and earnest carnie.

Exciting banners promise fun new experiences for your brain!
Carrying the flag comes with extra benefits and a uniform upgrade.
He also has a master's degree in 18th-century French poetry.
Bashes plants with a heavy barbell just to prove how strong and manly he is.
At the same time, though, you wouldn't want to bet your life on these guys only coming out of cannons.
Carnie Imp Split is pursuing solo opportunities, as is Carnie Imp Split.
Separating Carnie Imp Twins creates two Carnie Imp Splits.
They're not actually twins, though they are identical.
Two imps are generously provided for the price of one.
He's such an evil magician that he'll reveal all his secrets for a shiny nickel.
Magician Zombie vanishes zombies and himself forward on the board, and he's got sneaky doves who'll try to fly off with your plants.
At such a towering height, Stiltwalker Zombie has an elevated view of things. He refuses, for example, to buy second-hand milk.
Stiltwalker Zombie's stilts allow him to walk right over most plants.
Once released onto the lawn chickens run full speed to peck at your brains.

{FLAVOR}After publishing the fourth study on Ornithology, and four years of research at the Hadron Collider, Chicken Wrangler Zombie has finally solved the riddle of what came first.
Releases a flock of chickens once his baling wire is broken.
{FLAVOR}The sheriff of these here parts. Please pull over the horse and pull out your driver's license, registration, and proof of brains.
His cowhide cone gives him twice the toughness of a regular cowboy.
{FLAVOR}A five-time winner of the temporal chili cook-off. Those Egyptian zombies don't know their chili, but Cowboys love their beans. The more you eat, the more you brains.
His chili pot hat makes him greatly resistant to damage.
{FLAVOR}Cart-Head Zombie could probably move a lot faster if he did a handstand and rolled, but he's not thinking that far ahead.
Cart-head Zombie's cart-shaped chapeau provides extra-wheeled head protection.
{FLAVOR}Cowboy Zombie thinks he's the roughest, toughest, meanest zombie varmint in the west, south and east. He's anxious to test his skills in the central coast region.
Marks the arrival of a huge dusty "wave" of zombies.
{FLAVOR}Arrows point to the brain on Cowboy Rally's Flag, as if to say, "Hey, everyone, I would like to emphasize this image." It's canny design.
Cowboy Rally Zombie marks the appearance of a sizable stampede of zombies.

{FLAVOR}Likes candy.
{FLAVOR}Conehead Peasant is just happy to have a cone over his head. Times are tough, man. He knows a lot of zombies don't even have that.
His stony turret cone makes him twice as tough as normal peasants.

{FLAVOR}None of the other zombies seem to understand just how versatile Buckethead Peasant's choice of headwear is. Sure, his bucket makes for a great battle helmet. But just last night, he cooked a truly divine brain stew in it. And next time you see his band, check out what he’s using for a kick drum.
His forged bucket provides great protection from damage.

{FLAVOR}Knight Zombie was just as surprised as anyone when Zombie King promoted him. He'd never say this out loud, but he's not sure he deserves the position. He's not sure he has what it takes to wear the armor. But like they say, "Fake it 'til you make it."
His king appointed helm provides amazing protection from damage.
{FLAVOR}Someone shouted, "Bring out your undead!" And then Peasant Zombie found himself here. He simply doesn't remember anything that happened before that.

{FLAVOR}They keep telling Peasant Zombie that there is no greater reward than being granted the banner to carry into battle. But when he sees other Peasant Zombies being granted cones, buckets, and even helms, he thinks maybe they're making that up so they don't hurt his feelings.
Marks the arrival of a huge dark "wave" of zombies.

{KEYWORD}Damage: {STAT}crushes plants with hammer
{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}launches Imp Monk when damaged

{FLAVOR}When Dark Ages Gargantuar wants to find pantaloons that fit him, he has to shop at the "Enormous & Towering" store. He hates it though. It's embarrassing. He just wants to shop for clothes where all the other zombies shop.
Immense zombie who brings the hammer down.
{FLAVOR}Frankly, Imp Monk Zombie decided to don the robes because of the sweet haircut that went with them.
Summoned past most of your defenses, then shambles onward.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}Immune to fire damage

{FLAVOR}Imp Zombie knows he's too old to wear a dragon costume like a kid on Halloween. But he doesn't care. Let the others judge. His spirit animal is a dragon, and he feels closer to his true self when he's dressed like this.
Spit past most of your defenses, then claws forward.

{FLAVOR}Oh sure, everyone loves to laugh at Jester Zombie's clownish routines. But what no one knows is that he has a Master of Fine Arts from the Chewliard Performing Arts School. Heck, he's been on stage with some of the finest classical theatre companies this side of the lawn. But sometimes you just gotta go where the paycheck is.
Returns projectiles that are shot at him.

{FLAVOR}As Shakespeare once wrote, "Uneasy lies the head that wears a crown." And Zombie King couldn't agree more. It is incredibly difficult to get a good night's sleep with a crown on your head. That thing is all kinds of uncomfortable.
Grants knight helms to nearby peasant zombies.

{FLAVOR}All the zombies agree, Wizard Zombie's powers of transmutation are impressive. But what they don't get is ... why sheep? Everyone knows it would be more helpful if the Wizard used his powers to turn plants into, say, more zombies. But yeah, no one is going to say that to his face.
Jurassic Conehead Zombie is trying to get the jump on the whole "traffic cone" idea. He figures it'll be a HUGE market in about 150 million years.
Cones, or old leftover horns bundled together with string so that they look sort of like a cone, provide some middling protection.
The real question, the burning mystery, is: where did he find blue fur for his outfit?
Crude drawings of buckets provide as much protection as the real thing.
Contrary to his name, Jurassic Fossilhead's fossil head isn't actually a fossil. That skull's maybe a week and a half old, tops.
Fossil skulls not only provide a huge amount of damage absorption, but are also extremely classy.
{FLAVOR}If you were to extract DNA from the Amberhead Zombie and combine it with the DNA of a frog, you'd probably be breaking the law at some point.
Amberhead Zombie's head-engulfing ball of amber provides hardened protection.
Jurassic Bully is slow, stupid, and smells bad. But hey, at least he's punctual.
A trudging, damage-resistant zombie who is immune to Primal Peashooter's knockback.
{FLAVOR}Somebody tied rocks to Jurassic Rockpuncher's hands. Being unable to remove them (because he had rocks tied to his hands), he was left with no choice but to roll with it.
Jurassic Rockpuncher pummels plants with rocks tied to his hands.
Jurassic Zombie is NOT primitive. See, he's wearing a tie and everything!
Regular beard-having zombie from the unimaginable past.
He's not only got a flag, but he's also got a can-do attitude and a fierce hunger for success. Success and brains.
Marks the arrival of a huge epochal "wave" of highly anachronistic zombies.

{FLAVOR}Where did Jurassic Rally Zombie get his fancy new flag? Nobody knows. It's a mystery. The police should look into it. Or maybe we could get a fund together and hire a detective. It's a real puzzle.
Jurassic Rally Zombie marks the arrival of large group of zombies.

{KEYWORD}Damage: {STAT}crushes plants with bone
{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}launches Jurassic Imp when damaged
{FLAVOR}Jurassic Gargantuar wonders how there can be zombies millions of years before the advent of humanity. He doesn't let it get in the way of his plant-bashing, though.
This nasty little nipper can make a serious dent in your defenses if left to his own devious devices.
A weaker, smaller, much more vicious version of the typical Jurassic zombie.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}summons disco Jetpack Zombies

{FLAVOR}After some initial problems with the sideburn suspension system, the Disco-tron 3000 went on to become the shufflin' dance-bot of doom it is today.
Drops in disco zombies when dropping the beat.

{KEYWORD}Damage: {STAT}crushes plants with sarcophagus
{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}launches Imp Mummy when damaged

{FLAVOR}True fact #1: The pyramids were built in an attempt to make Mummified Gargantuar seem small. It didn't work. True fact #2: The Sphinx isn't missing its nose... that is the face of... Gargantuar.
Massive zombie from a royal line of mummies.
{FLAVOR}Imp Mummy prefers to laze around the tomb, hop up on the urns, and scratch at the sarcophagi. The sound of him coughing up a hairball is one you will never forget.
Thrown over most of your defenses, then slinks onward.
Being made out of light and positional co-ordinates has no effect on this erzatz zombie’s ravenous hunger for tangy brains.
Pixelated zombie generated by super cool arcade machine. Comes in regular, cone and bucket flavors.
When it’s a choice between quarters for games and quarters for laundry, Arcade Zombie is prepared to make the ultimate stinky sacrifice.
Pushes an arcade cabinet that spits out 8-Bit Zombies.
Neon Conehead Zombie used to be a big believer in de-evolution, but then he forgot what it meant.
Cones provide protection and focus the sound of righteous tunes.
Neon Buckethead Zombie had to go all the way to the dump to find a headband he really liked.
Buckets absorb damage because that’s just what they do.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT} boom box has no effect on ground plants and Phat Beets

{FLAVOR}Boombox Zombie doesn’t want to buy, sell or process anything; he just really wants to consume your brains.
Holds aloft a boom box that tranquilizes all plants with its heartfelt tunes.
Delivers only the freshest moves at bargain basement prices.
Kicks zombies forward when transported by the power of rap.
He's cutting down on his head-banging so as not to bang his head clean off.
Fluorescent colors and little yellow plastic strips are the marks of a truly hip, groundbreaking new style of zombie wave flag.
Marks the arrival of a huge mixtape-making "wave" of zombies.

{KEYWORD}Damage: {STAT}crushes plants with guitar
{KEYWORD}Damage: {STAT}bashes sonic blast when metal music plays
{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}launches Impunk when damaged

{FLAVOR}Hair Metal Gargantuar only knows one chord, but you'd better believe he'll play it all night and then some.
Glitter Zombie inspires zombies everywhere to boogie their brains out, whether it's just one moment or maybe forever, or at least until the lights come on and they're kicking everybody out.
Trails glamorous rainbows that protect zombies behind her when she's feeling the beat.
Impunk’s lyrics have been described as "banal," "incoherent," and "totally expressive of the Zompunk movement at its finest."
Tossed past most of your defenses, then rocks out to your detriment.
MC Zom-B doesn’t want you to know it, but his fancy bling is really just gold-plated zinc he got from his grandma.
Spins microphone to damage nearby plants when he's dropping his sick, sick rhymes.

{KEYWORD}Weakness: {STAT}Magnet Shrooms pull off his head

{FLAVOR}Punk Zombie’s piercings represent his individuality and his belief in personal freedom, or maybe just that he fell face-first into a sewing machine.
Moshes plants back a space when his jam is playing.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}torch destroys plants on contact
{KEYWORD}Weakness: {STAT}cold attacks extinguish torch

{FLAVOR}His impressive friendly mutton chops have always kept food in them for weeks, making sure his explorations are filled with snacks.
Carries a torch that can instantly destroy your plants.
{FLAVOR}Torchlight Zombie has no fear of the dark. That's not because he's always got a torch, however, but rather because as a zombie he has no capacity for fear in the first place.
Carries a torch that instantly destroys plants and scorches the earth.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}pushes plants to the left instead of eating

{FLAVOR}Now past his prime, Mecha-Football Zombie is ready to be put back into the game. Until he gets some brains, concussions aren't a concern.
{FLAVOR}Has tried to calculate the volume of his mathematically perfect cone, but he always ends up dreaming about brain π.
His poly-polymer cone gives him twice the toughness of regular future zombie.
{FLAVOR}Other zombies call him old-fashioned for being nostalgic for the year 2008.  It was a simpler time when brains were brains, zombies were zombies, and those punk plants kept to themselves.
His techno-bucket greatly increases his protection from damage.
{FLAVOR}The force field gets its unique color from frequency harmonics and a liberal dose of purple paint.
Holo Head Zombie's head-mounted force field provides hyper-protection.
Future zombies look good in red shirts. Future fact #23: Nothing bad happens to red shirts.
{FLAVOR}Sometimes Future Flag Zombie regrets having to be at the bleeding edge of zombie wave advancement technology.
Marks the arrival of a huge future-proof "wave" of zombies.
{FLAVOR}If you look carefully, you'll notice that Robo-Rally Zombie's flag is a sophisticated piece of hovertech combined with a stick.
Robo-Rally Zombie and his flag marks the arrival of an above-average number of zombies.

{KEYWORD}Damage: {STAT}crushes plants with arms
{KEYWORD}Damage: {STAT}randomly burns tiles with laser eyes
{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}launches Bug Bot when damaged

{FLAVOR}The imp pilots of the Gargantuar Prime series are handpicked by Dr. Zomboss himself. They are the imp elite.  The small, the mean, and the fearless! But mostly the ones who can drive a stick shift.
Has it all: heavy armor, laser eyes, smashing arms, and Bug Bot deployment system.
{FLAVOR}He always wanted to "see the world," "be his own boss," and "meet and consume interesting brains." He still doesn't understand how he got stuck in this cramped Bug Bot job 24/7.
Lands on the lawn past your defenses, then hops forward.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}floats over low plants, boosts over most other plants
{KEYWORD}Weakness: {STAT}Tall blocking plants

{FLAVOR}The Jetpack Zombie was an early adopter during the brain acquisition tech explosion of 2113. Little did he know he would be stuck with version 1.0 of the simple jetpack.
Boosts to float over all but the tallest plant barriers.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}floats over low plants, boosts over most other plants
{KEYWORD}Weakness: {STAT}Tall blocking plants

{FLAVOR}A zombie who 'lives' for drama, he's an original cast member of the stage musical "Disco is BACK! For Revenge!" His signature dance move is "The Weed Whacker."
Boosts to float over all but the tallest plant barriers, in style.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}floats over low plants, boosts over most other plants
{KEYWORD}Weakness: {STAT}tall blocking plants

{FLAVOR}Blastronaut's rocket-pack is strictly ornamental; his hovering ability comes from a deep meditative state and from being full of helium.
Blastronaut Zombie boosts to float over all but the tallest plants.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}creates a shield to protect from incoming attacks

{FLAVOR}Shield Zombie developed his system using funds from a BiteStarter campaign. The push goal for pushing plants was not met.
Protect himself and nearby zombies with a force field.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}shield regenerates over time

{FLAVOR}Deflector Zombie saw what Shield Zombie was doing and said to himself, "BRAAAAAAINS," because that's really the only word zombies know.
Deflector Zombie protects himself with a powerful force field that stretches across 5 rows.
History records that Roman Caesar Zombie was a leader of impressive size and grandeur, looked up to by all his subjects.
Roman Caesar Zombie tosses imperial salad dressing onto plants, making them irresistibly delicious to zombies. He also promotes Roman Zombies, giving them stronger helmets.

Cardio Zombie is all about health, healthiness and healthy lifestyles. He refuses to consume carbs, downing nothing but high-protein brains for every meal. In his opinion, other zombies really need to up their game. NO EXCUSES!
Advances to a set spot on the board, then tosses buffing brains at other zombies until he's chased away or retreats on his own.
Z-Mech is taking time out from his PvZ Heroes and PvZ Garden Warfare duties to bring his unique brand of destruction to Plants vs. Zombies 2. Don't worry, though; he's cleared it with his manager.
Deploys a set of summoning and teleportation technologies to harass, damage and otherwise imperil plants on the board.

{FLAVOR}Cave Conehead Zombie was the first zombie to invent the cone. He lashed the horn of a mammoth to a slab of petrified wood ... and boom! A cone! The invention of the cone changed everything for the zombies. EVERYTHING.
His mammoth horn cone makes him twice as tough as normal cave-dwellers.

{FLAVOR}Cave Buckethead Zombie likes rocks. He likes rocks A LOT. He strapped a rock to his head and called it a bucket. None of the other Cave Zombies know what a "bucket" is, but they like his style.
His stone "bucket" hat provides great protection from damage.

{FLAVOR}One day, a Cave Zombie fell head-first into a glacial stream. It had been a bad day already, so he lay there in the frigid water for a long time contemplating the insignificance of his life. When he finally stood up, he discovered that his head was encased in ice. At last, his life had meaning! He was unique! He was Blockhead Zombie! At least, that's his story and he's sticking to it.
The ice block on his head provides amazing protection from damage.

{FLAVOR}Cave Zombie was busy painting handprints on cave walls when he was told to start fighting plants. He's not sure why he's fighting plants, but he hopes he can get back to painting soon. He was feeling inspired. He had plans for some big pieces. Art school was finally paying off.

{FLAVOR}Dodo Rider believes dodos are the future of transportation. He believes a public dodo-riding system is not only a wise expenditure of tax dollars but would help the vast majority of zombies get where they need to go more efficiently. Everyone keeps telling him there's no future in dodos, but he refuses to listen.
Dodo bird with an imp rider. The dodo can flap and jump over barricades as well as troublesome plants.

{FLAVOR}Cave Flag Zombie has been in the flag-carrying business for a long time. It's been his life's work. He's good at it. But sometimes, just sometimes, he longs for a change. He wonders if he could be good at something else. He wonders if he could leave it all behind and start fresh. He's pretty sure he's having a mid-life crisis.
Marks the arrival of a huge frosty "wave" of zombies.

{KEYWORD}Damage: {STAT}crushes plants with icicle
{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}fires off Yeti Imps when damaged

{FLAVOR}Somewhere along the line, Sloth Gargantuar contracted a bad case of Yeti Imps. He used soap, medicinal powders, and a salve made from sloth slobber in an attempt to get rid of them ... to no avail. But the truth is, he's grown used to their presence. The darn things are itchy. They're always squabbling. They nag him endlessly. But at this point, he'd probably miss them if they ever cleared up.
Massive sloth skinned zombie with a case of the imps. Carries and throws three imps instead of just one.
{FLAVOR}Shhhhh ... Hunter Zombie didn't actually kill that sabertooth tiger. He found the skin at a thrift store. Also, he's a vegetarian. Tell no one.
Zombie that can throw snow balls at range to cool down plants until they freeze into blocks.

{FLAVOR}Yeti Imp recently took up knitting. He started with a scarf, moved on to mittens and eventually knitted an entire bodysuit out of hair he shaved off of Yeti Zombie. He just loves knitting. When those needles are in his hands, he feels a sense of calm he's never felt before.
Thrown over most of your defenses, then ambles onward.

{FLAVOR}Troglobite has been pushing ice blocks across the tundra day in and day out for as long as he can remember. It's cold and exhausting work, and frankly, he's ready for a vacation. He'd like to go somewhere sunny and warm for a change. He'd like to relax in the sand. He hears Big Wave Beach is nice this time of year.
Strong zombie that can push blocks of ice across the lawn.
Once released, weasels run full speed even over ice floes to nibble your brains.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}releases zombie ice weasels when damaged
{FLAVOR}Weasel Hoarder claims she's the one who wrote the song "Pop! Goes the Weasel." And for eons now, she's been demanding royalties for it. But everyone just ignores her. They know that Weasel Hoarder can't even carry a tune, much less write a catchy ditty about the sound vermin make when hugged a bit too tightly.
Zombie hiding in a log with a pack of snow weasels. Weasels are released when her log is shattered.
They carry no memory of the zombie they’d been before.
Zombies converted into Imps by Imp Pear become Imp Pear Imps.
{FLAVOR}Given the rarity of traffic in the jungle, it’s a mystery how Conehead Adventurer managed to acquire his headgear. Maybe he ordered it online?
His makeshift cone gives him twice the toughness of a normal explorer zombie.
{FLAVOR}Armed with his sturdy kettle and even sturdier moustache, Kettlehead Adventurer is ready to ruin your day and possibly make a stew.
His kettle-bucket gives him great resistance to damage.
Bug Zombie and Bug make a great team, partly because Bug gives Bug Zombie great mobility, but mostly because they share an intense disinterest in horses.
Bug carries zombie in over ground defenses and lifts him over barriers.
{FLAVOR}Adventurer Zombie was certain he was the first to rediscover the Lost City. He was less certain after he ran into another 50 Adventurer Zombies at the gift shop.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}throws Lost City Imp when damaged

{FLAVOR}Porter Gargantuar actually provided the bulk of the funding for the expedition. And most of the bulk all around, come to think of it.
{FLAVOR}Nepotism got Lost City Imp where he is. He’s Bug Zombie’s second cousin thrice removed, but he parlayed that connection into a sweet gig getting carried around in a little box.
Gets tossed past most defenses, then explores on foot.
Parasol Zombie desperately wants to get to the opera before the curtain rises. She’s not going to make it, though, because it’s thousands of miles away on another continent.
Parasol provides protection from lobbed projectiles.
No one ever presumes that he’s Dr. Unlivingstone. Just once, though, he wishes that someone would.
His expedition cone makes him twice as tough as normal adventurers.
Buckethead Adventurer’s greatest discovery was that one morning, without warning or reason, there was a bucket on his head.
His rugged bucket provides considerable protection from damage.
Bug Zombie and Bug make a great team, partly because Bug gives Bug Zombie great mobility, but mostly because they share an intense disinterest in horses.
Bug carries zombie in over ground defenses and lifts him over barriers.
Unlike the more famous crystal skulls, turquoise skulls are totally non-mysterious and common as dirt.
Uses skull to steal sun, then unleashes energy in a destructive beam.
Adventurer Zombie just went looking for a jolly good show, and somehow ended up in the Lost City. “Hmm. Yes. Quite.” is all that he would say on the matter.

{KEYWORD}Damage: {STAT}blocks incoming projectiles, but is vulnerable to lobbed shots

{FLAVOR}Excavator Zombie once heard a song about having a hammer. He liked the idea, but decided it was too mainstream for him – so he got a shovel. Now he’s confident that he’s clearly the coolest zombie, the others are just too jealous to admit it.
Digs up plants and throws them behind him.
Flag Adventurer Zombie is always shouting "Tally ho!" as he leads the charge. At least, he's shouting it in his head.
Marks the arrival of an intrepid “wave” of zombies.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}throws Lost City Imp when damaged

{FLAVOR}Porter Gargantuar dreams of the discovery that will make him powerful and influential. Maybe then the Imps will be the one carrying him around. It's always nice to have dreams.
{FLAVOR}Nepotism got Lost City Imp where he is. He’s Bug Zombie’s second cousin thrice removed, but he parlayed that connection into a sweet gig getting carried around in a little box.
Gets tossed past most defenses, then explores on foot.
Imp Porter is stronger than he looks. He’s also more charming, smarter and has a better education.
Drops pack on Gold Tile; pack becomes tent from which zombies emerge.

Wealthy beyond reason, the Parasol Zombie lived a life of luxury – when what she craved was a life of adventure. She funded the expedition to the Lost City and set out to see its wonders for herself, never forgetting to bring her trusty parasol. “In case it rains,” she explained – but it only came out sounding like “Brains.”
Parasol provides protection from lobbed projectiles.
He faked his pilot's license and figured nobody would notice. But they did.
Relic Hunter has hunted some pretty impressive relics in his day. Idols, antiques, curios... he’s hunted 'em all.
{FLAVOR}Zombie engineers considered the orange cone the height of zombie protective technology. It wasn't until they perfected the design for the Robo-Cone that someone remembered the bucket.
The armor-plated cone offers phenomenal protection for its pilot.
All-Star Zombie is a third-round draft pick and shows a lot of promise, but come on, his salary demands are beyond ridiculous. Ten million brains per year? For FIFTY YEARS?
A heavy-duty zombie who charges your defensive line.
Balloon zombie has no idea where the balloon came from, but he's going with it and he's open to seeing where it takes him.
Balloon carries zombies over barriers and ground defenses.
You can't really blame him for getting so upset; he was THIS close to finishing the crossword (23 down was "Brains.")
Newspaper protects zombie, who is then enraged when it is destroyed.
Super-Fan Imp has season tickets, subscribes to the team newsletter, and is super pumped about exploding on contact with fans of the opposing team.
An all-too-enthusiastic imp who explodes with rah-rah-rah fervor.
{FLAVOR}Conehead Mummy Zombie prefers the circular cone shape over the typical pyramid shape. It's a fashion thing, and Conehead Mummy Zombie always stays ahead of fashion.
His cobra cone headdress makes him twice as tough as normal mummies.
{FLAVOR}Buckethead Mummy Zombie graduated Magna Zom Louder from Zombie Academy where he learned to utilize his diaphragm during groaning lessons.
His sandy bucket greatly protects him from damage.
{FLAVOR}Pyramid-Head Zombie isn't aware that his pyramid is pyramid-shaped. He's a little slow in that respect.
His pyramid-shaped headgear provides triangular noggin protection.
{FLAVOR}Is he a mummy? Is he a zombie? It turns out he's a zombie who's rolled himself in toilet paper to protect his fair skin. True fact!
{FLAVOR}Egyptian Flag Zombie is so far behind he thinks he's in first place. He's clearly living in de-Nile.
Marks the arrival of a huge sandy "wave" of zombies.

{FLAVOR}Sometimes, a regular Flag Mummy Zombie simply isn't enough to inspire the desired amount of terror and disgust. In these instances, upgrading to the Egypt Rally Zombie isn't the sensible choice, it's the only choice.
He celebrates with increased vigor and truculence the arrival of a new wave of bandaged baddies.
{FLAVOR}Sunday Edition Zombie REALLY loves the comics section, which is why his rage is so all-consuming when it is torn to tatters before he's finished reading it.
The newspaper protects zombie, who becomes enraged when it is destroyed.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}floats over low plants

{FLAVOR}The Pelican Zombie upgraded from the Seagull Zombie and has no regrets. No egrets, either. Just a pelican.
Pelican Zombie crosses water without a plank and flies over low plants.

{KEYWORD}Speed Details: {STAT}moves like a hungry zombie once free

{FLAVOR}The second cousin once removed of King Rot, he rose to power with his disappearing sarcophagus act, but met his untimely end in an unfortunate goat accident. His tale is told in great detail on the back of his sarcophagus, which no one will ever see.
His sarcophagus greatly protects him but slows down a rather fast zombie.

{KEYWORD}Damage: {STAT}crushes plants with piano
{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}causes cowboy zombies to switch lanes

{FLAVOR}Pianist Zombie only knows two songs, and they're both groaners.
His rolling piano crushes plants while his music causes dancing zombies to switch lanes.
{FLAVOR}Conehead Pirate is a simple zombie. When asked what his favorite dish is, he'd think for a moment, straighten his ascot, and say, "Rrurrarrbrains." Perhaps he could borrow a cup, neighbor?
His Jolly Roger cone makes him twice as tough as normal pirates.
{FLAVOR}Buckethead Pirate Zombie is looking for his bucket. Have you seen it? It's where? Up where? Speak up, he can't hear you.
His sturdy wooden bucket provides excellent protection from damage.
{FLAVOR}Dredged from the deepest of seas, Barrelhead Zombie's barrel is a high-quality cask that fits just a bit too snugly.
Barrelhead Zombie's keg-like hat provides augmented protection.
{FLAVOR}What could it be? Could it be gold? Or some sort of other kind of treasure?  Who knows!
Contains Imp Zombies that launch out when destroyed.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}parrot pet steals plants

{FLAVOR}Pirate Captain Zombie isn't actually a captain.  His dry cleaning got mixed up with someone else's, but he thought he looked cool with an eye patch.  Plus, the parrot already knew his name, so he just went with it.
His parrot can fly away with your plant and then return to him.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}can fly to plants in other lanes to carry them away

{FLAVOR}He's a third generation aviation revolutionary. He wants to serve his pirate brethren like his father and his grandmother, Salty Anne, before him.
Quickly flies from the Captain to carry away a plant.
{FLAVOR}Keeping up with the latest pirate trends is always tricky, but remember, he was planking before it was cool.
Marks the arrival of a huge salty "wave" of zombies.
{FLAVOR}Jolly Roger Zombie and his flag are fused together into a single brain-munching unit. Their teamwork is an inspiration to ghouls everywhere.
Jolly Roger Zombie marks the arrival of lots and lots of zombies.

{KEYWORD}Damage: {STAT}crushes plants with shark
{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}fires off Pirate Imp when damaged

{FLAVOR}Gargantuar Pirate likes short walks off the plank, moonlit raiding parties, and the smell of cannon fire. A true romantic.
Enormous zombie who redefines the shark attack.
{FLAVOR}He was a bootblack, with a side trade as a pickpocket on the streets of London, but all he stole were oversized footwear. "Time to steal some booty!" was his catchphrase.
Prefers the compact space of barrels, both cannon and rolling.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}randomly wears a protective metal grate

{FLAVOR}The grate is his most prized possession. The poncho is there just to protect it from getting rusty. Also, he's looking for his mechanical horse.
Sometimes has a hidden armored plate.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}appears on the left side of the lawn after dynamite explodes

{FLAVOR}"There once was a zombie who got old, spending all his days looking for gold.  'Til one day in the rain, he finally ate brains... and, wait, where's his other shoe?"
Launches over your defenses when his fuse burns down.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}tries to steal sun

{FLAVOR}Ra Zombie isn't actually named after the Sun God Ra, though that's a common mistake. He just likes to say “Ra” a lot.
Tries to steal sun, just for safe keeping.
Was there enough traffic in Ancient Rome to justify cones? Historians differ. It's a real debate.
A traffic cone made of marble provides some protection.
They had buckets just like this back in Ancient Rome. Believe it.
A fancy bucket with a bit of flair distinguishes this zombie.
Did you know that in Ancient Rome, a centurion commanded a century? Isn't that wild?
A higher grade of Roman Zombie.
Bust Head Zombie belongs in museum with a big sign that says something like, "WARNING: THIS IS A ZOMBIE!"
A bust head means this Roman zombie can take a serious beating.
Surprise! That exploding vase has a zombie in it! Isn’t that surprising?
A ballista from Ancient Rome, the Zcorpion Zombie launches an exploding vase at the nearest plant in its lane.
In Ancient Rome, flags were often used on the battlefield to direct troop movements. Though come on: how much direction do you really need to shuffle leftward?
The flag indicates more zombies are on their way!
He's got a column and he's not afraid to use it.
Wears a helmet. Throws an imp AND a net. Just a real piece of work.
Hot tip: take this one out as fast as you can if you don't want your life turned into a pit of abject misery and despair.
Uses weird Roman magic to heal zombies.

Small. Impy. Wears a former lion.

Zombie Medusa pushes petrified zombies in stone blocks as well as stoneifying zombies and zomboids that face her.
The shield protects him from bad reviews and hurtful remarks.
A dull-witted, unusually shy Roman zombie who's also carrying a shield.
When three Roman shield zombies are too many, how about two? Two's a good number, right? It's even, it's prime... it's got everything!
A pair of Roman shield zombies.
This number of shield zombies is three higher than zombies can count.
Three Roman shield zombies in a row.

{FLAVOR}Seagull Zombie has racked up the frequent flier miles and dreams of going to the top colleges in the world on a cerebral gastronomy vacation.
Crosses watery gaps without a plank and flies over low plants.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}lands four tiles into your lawn

{FLAVOR}He swashes. He buckles. But, he also writes home every third Sunday and sends brains and treasure via post. He's a good zombie at heart.
Swings in on a rope to land midway onto your lawn.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}creates tombstones on the lawn

{FLAVOR}He dreams about playing fetch, running for the brains. He loves burying himself in the yard, and is not yet indoor trained. He's still looking for his tail.
Throws out bones to create tombstones.

{KEYWORD}Speed Details: {STAT}runs away after a short while
{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}carries treasure

{FLAVOR}The rare and wondrous Yeti carries his lunch box up and down Mount Brainer to his isolated mountain lodge.
A rare and curious creature, he always packs a lunch.
{FLAVOR}After a wild night, Conehead Zombie woke up holding a mysterious receipt for a cone and industrial strength adhesive.
His traffic cone headpiece makes him twice as tough as normal zombies.

{FLAVOR}There was a time when Buckethead Zombie was hailed as a zombie genius for his innovative bucket-on-head strategy. It's been a few years, though, and zombies wonder if he's got any surprises left. His secret? He doesn't.
His bucket hat makes him extremely resistant to damage.
{FLAVOR}After consultation with various storybook wolves, it was determined that straw helmets and wood helmets were not up to snuff, and that brick helmets had to be seriously considered.
Brickhead Zombie's brick head provides thorough brickheaded brickheadness.
{FLAVOR}Basic Zombie hates the term “Basic.” He doesn't  consider himself some generic foe or common corpse. He's an individual, darn it, and he's going to make a difference even if it kills you.
{FLAVOR}A spelling impaired zombie named "Brian," Flag Zombie keeps thinking the rest of the zombies are talking to him. At least he feels important.
His flag marks the arrival of a huge pile or "wave" of zombies.
{FLAVOR}Rally Zombie splurged on the all-leather flag because, heck, he's worth it.
Rally Zombie and his flag marks the arrival of a large clot or "pile" of zombies.

{KEYWORD}Damage: {STAT}crushes plants with pole

{FLAVOR}Gargantuar is the embodiment of power, made real. He is a juggernaut of hunger, from which there is no escape. He is fear unleashed. Well, he's fear slightly leashed.
Gargantuar really is kind of a big deal.
{FLAVOR}What he lacks in reach he more than makes up for with his bad attitude, or zombadittude as he likes to call it. Don't encourage him.
Is hurled onto the lawn past your defenses, then shuffles ahead.

{KEYWORD}Damage: {STAT}crushes plants with pole
{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}throws Imp when damaged

{FLAVOR}The ceramic confines of the Vase Gargantuar's home has done nothing to his endless hunger, his immense power, or his vast destructive potential. However, his footspeed could be better.
Phenomenally sized zombie stuffed into a tiny unliving space.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}launches a low flying imp rider over plants
{KEYWORD}Weakness: {STAT}Tall-nut blocks flying imp

{FLAVOR}He's not an angry bull. He loves flowers, playing in the fields, sitting under trees, and long walks across the pasture. He wants to settle down when he meets the right cow. Too bad he's a robot.
Can launch his zombie rider past most of your defenses.
{FLAVOR}"Legend" perhaps overstates Rodeo Legend Zombie's status in the rodeo world. Don't tell him that, though, unless you're desperate to hear an hour-long tirade about calf-roping.
Rodeo Legend Zombie smashes a plant and launches his zombie rider past most of your defenses.
{FLAVOR}Had dreams of becoming a rodeo clown but found the clown make-up to just be too creepy.
Gets launched past all but the tallest plants, then proceeds on foot.
ZCorp leads the field in large, cone-shaped pushpins for cranial safety.
A typical ZCorp employee, except with more on his mind.
ZCorp fully complies with all local, state and federal waste disposal ordinances.
An environmentally friendly recycle bin protects the employee's noggin from damage.
She works for ZCorp AND consults for them. Great gig if you can get it!
ZCorp Consultant disrupts your paradigm and tableflips your bluesky/redocean.
He was issued the standard ZCorp coffee mug at orientation.
ZCorp contractors may purchase ZCorp office supplies for a small fee.
It's the combination of notebook and comically large pushpin that really gives this contractor the edge.
ZCorp encourages its contractors to come up with out-of-the-box solutions for keeping their heads safe.
Recycle bins make excellent and environmentally friendly headgear.
ZCorp is so inclusive, they even give contractors free coffee mugs.
ZCorp developed its flag logo in-house and is very proud of it.
The flag is a tremendous way to create brand awareness while also indicating a lot more zombies are about to appear and eat your brains.
Head Office Impgantuar's door is always open. It is, however, highly inadvisable to take him up on that offer.
His giant noggin is a blunt instrument of smashing.
ZCorp HelpDesk is here to help, especially if what you need help with is having too many plants on your lawn.
ZCorp HelpDesk drops in and throws an exploding laptop.
Gargimp Legal delivers cease-and-desists the old-fashioned way: with a baseball bat.
Tiny but fierce, the Gargimp Legal department is the best and the beast in the business.
Zcorp Chair Racer brings fun and spontaneity to the zcorporate experience.
Zcorp Chair Racer zooms in at high speed, collides with great impact, and catapults leftward with extraordinary grace.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}mouth turbine can pull plants to it
{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}summoned zombie sharks can consume plants

{FLAVOR}The Zombot Sharktronic Sub is a true labor of love. Dr. Zomboss obsessed over every detail of the aquatic mechanism of doom as he worked on it day in and day out from the wee hours of the morning until well after dark. He carefully handcrafted the shark's nearly impenetrable exterior skin. He shaved each razor-sharp tooth to a point by hand. And he painstakingly installed the lethal plant-consuming fan inside the machine's horrific maw all by himself. Zomboss shed more than one tear of joy when his masterpiece was complete. Say what you will about the evil genius, but he is passionate about his projects.
The ravenous engine of carnage from the murky depths.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}can launch Cannonball Imps

{FLAVOR}"Despite the decline of circuses in recent years, I refuse to give up on a form of entertainment with so much history and plant-destroying potential," cackles Dr. Zomboss, all while tapping out a jaunty little tune on his keyboard.
The mystery-filled circus-wagon of terrors and delights.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}missile attacks can target mine carts

{FLAVOR}Ranchers and farmhands abandon your fields. Rumbling down the dusty trail, this wagon was engineered to strike fear into the heart of any horticulturist who should encounter it. Dr. Zomboss normally doesn't take any bull, but this time he made an exception.
The stagecoach of destruction from the western wilds.

{KEYWORD}Damage: {STAT}fire breathing attacks destroy plants
{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}lobbed fireballs can hatch Imp Dragon Zombies

{FLAVOR}With a rumble of destruction, Dr. Zomboss forged his Dark Dragon in the heart of a volcano. Then he tempered the beast in the chilled waters of Doom Lake. Finally  he fed its furnace with coal from the Mines of Morbidity. And the paint job - that was done by Carl.
The desolator of all, from dark times.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}summons dinosaurs

{FLAVOR}With flagrant disregard for temporal tidiness and simple good taste, Dr. Zomboss figured it would be a good idea to build a big metal dinosaur.
A mechanical means of dinosaurian destruction.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}missile attack can create tombstones

{FLAVOR}To add that extra bit of wickedness to the Sphinx-inator Dr. Zomboss chiseled his creation from the stonework of cursed tombs. You should not take this instance of reuse and recycle to mean he's going green. The only thing green about him is his tongue.
The destroyer of plants from the ancient sands.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}speakers do passive damage (except to ground plants and Phat Beet) and send out shockwave attacks

{FLAVOR}In another world, in another time, Dr. Zomboss would receive the bounty of enthusiastic applause that is his due. Not here and now, though. Nope.
An intimate evening with some of Dr. Zomboss’ most recent and painful explorations.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}missile attacks can destroy Power Tiles

{FLAVOR}When Dr. Zomboss is nestled into the comfy folds of his futuristic cerebral control pod he almost finds it hard to be evil. Of course once he sees a lawn full of happy plants that puts him right back where he needs to be, hungry and evil.
The Power Tile crushing creation from the Far Future.

{FLAVOR}Dr. Zomboss was real impressed with himself when he came up with the idea to build a weaponized woolly mammoth with the power to blast snow and ice out of its mechanical trunk. But what Dr. Zomboss didn’t realize until it was too late: He’s allergic to mammoth fur. Now he has to load up on allergy medication every time he wants to take the darn thing out for a spin.
The mammoth mech with an ice blast from the past.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT} drops zombies and bags o’ sand

{FLAVOR}After repeated failures with variously robotic engines of destruction, Dr. Zomboss decided to go with a kinder, more eco-friendly lighter-than-air option to sow disaster and discord.
The floating fortress from the skies above.

{KEYWORD}Special: {STAT}cannon can rain down imps past your defenses

{FLAVOR}"Hoist the mizzenmast, batten down the hatches! 15 zombies on a dead man's boat, yo ho ho and a bucket of brains!" Dr. Zomboss had to admit he was really getting into this whole pirate thing. Though he never thought he'd be on a boat on a boat.
The plant plundering privateer of the high seas.
